Financial Controller		Kamylon Holdings		Wellesley Hills, MA		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong>THE INDIVIDUAL</strong> </p><p>  </p><p>Characterized as a hard working and driven individual, the Financial Controller is a fact-based, analytical and highly motivated self-starter who works well as part of a senior leadership team. </p><p></p><p><strong>Principal Focus of the Position:</strong> </p><p>  </p><p>The Controller will be responsible for implementing and generating high quality financial plans and operating statements and other management reports (financial and operational) on a weekly and monthly basis as well as providing ad hoc financial analysis and reporting and leading all annual audit and financial reporting-related activities.  He/she will also own data quality and reporting from our ERP system. </p><p>The Controller will have a dual reporting relationship to the Business Unit President and Kamylon’s Chief Financial Officer.</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong>THE COMPANY</strong> </p><p>  </p><p>Kamylon Holdings is a diversified Managerial Holding Company comprised of strategic business units which serve various industry markets. We invest in and provide ownership transition solutions to Large Local businesses with revenues of $8-80 million and cash flows of $1-8 million. We implement the proprietary Kamylon Management System (KMS) to continuously improve and consistently grow each business unit to the next level while extending the legacy of its original owner/entrepreneur. For additional information please visit Kamylon’s website at www.kamylon.com.</p></div>